nd deeply moving, Like Crazy is a warm and engrossing memoir about mental illness, reinvention, and the remarkable power of community. Lovingly told, Mathews's memoir is also a profound meditation on the joys and pitfalls of caring for an aging family member and of the remarkable growth that takes place as a child steps into the role of the parent"--cProvided by publisher.10aMathews, Dan.10aMathews, Perry LawrencexMental health. 0aSchizophrenicszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aSchizophrenicsxFamily relationshipszUnited States. 0aMothers and sonszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aLarge type books.  c(OCoLC)1193114077  c4631d4631